==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[acquisitio]]'', from ''[[acquirere]]'': compare French ''acquisition''. See [[acquire]]
===Noun===
'''aquisition'''
#The act or process of acquiring. The acquisition or loss of a province. - [[w:Thomas Babington Macaulay]].
#The thing acquired or gained; an acquirement; a gain; as, learning is an acquisition.

===Synonyms===
*See [[acquirement]].

